readiness.insight: Based on your current VO2 Max of 33.4 ml/kg/min, which indicates a sedentary fitness level, coupled with your sedentary activity level and no workout frequency, you are not yet fully prepared for climbing Freel Peak. This mountain is rated as difficult with an elevation of 3,318 meters. To improve your readiness, consider incorporating regular cardiovascular exercise, strength training, and gradually increasing your stamina through long-distance walking or running. Aim for at least 3-4 days of moderate exercise per week and gradually work up to more intense climbs. Additionally, ensure proper nutrition and stay hydrated, especially given the mountain's snowy conditions that may affect weather patterns.
